    "body": "\n## Purpose\n* [recent refactoring ](https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/31169) impacted ROCm fp8 static quant\n* assigned tensor to a parameter\n* CI caught the issue, but was on soft fail: https://buildkite.com/vllm/amd-ci/builds/2168/steps/canvas\n* PR resolves issue by using the replace_parameter semantics\n* stacked: https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm/pull/31321\n\n## Test Plan\n\n```bash\nMODEL := \"amd/Mixtral-8x7B-Instruct-v0.1-FP8-KV\"\n\nlaunch:\n\tVLLM_ROCM_USE_AITER=1 VLLM_ROCM_USE_AITER_MOE=1 vllm serve {{MODEL}} -tp 1 --enforce-eager\n\neval LIMIT:\n\tlm_eval \\\n\t\t--model local-completions \\\n\t\t--tasks gsm8k \\\n\t\t--model_args \"model={{MODEL}},base_url=http://localhost:8000/v1/completions,num_concurrent=100,tokenized_requests=False\" \\\n\t\t--limit {{LIMIT}}\n```\n\n## Test Result\n```bash\nlocal-completions (model=amd/Mixtral-8x7B-Instruct-v0.1-FP8-KV,base_url=http://localhost:8000/v1/completions,num_concurrent=100,tokenized_requests=False), gen_kwargs: (None), limit: 100.0, num_fewshot: None, batch_size: 1\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value|   |Stderr|\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|----:|---|-----:|\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  | 0.63|±  |0.0485|\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  | 0.63|±  |0.0485|\n```\n\n---\n<details>\n<summary> Essential Elements of an Effective PR Description Checklist </summary>\n\n- [ ] The purpose of the PR, such as \"Fix some issue (link existing issues this PR will resolve)\".\n- [ ] The test plan, such as providing test command.\n- [ ] The test results, such as pasting the results comparison before and after, or e2e results\n- [ ] (Optional) The necessary documentation update, such as updating `supported_models.md` and `examples` for a new model.\n- [ ] (Optional) Release notes update. If your change is user facing, please update the release notes draft in the [Google Doc](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YyVqrgX4gHTtrstbq8oWUImOyPCKSGnJ7xtTpmXzlRs/edit?tab=t.0).\n</details>\n\n",
